    <h2>Resources for Youth Mental Health</h2>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>National Suicide Prevention Lifeline</strong>: Provides free, confidential support 24/7 for
        individuals in distress. <a href="https://suicidepreventionlifeline.org/">Website</a></li>
      <li><strong>The Trevor Project</strong>: Offers crisis intervention and suicide prevention services to LGBTQ+
        youth. <a href="https://www.thetrevorproject.org/">Website</a></li>
      <li><strong>Crisis Text Line</strong>: Text-based support for those in crisis, available 24/7. <a
          href="https://www.crisistextline.org/">Website</a></li>
      <li><strong>NAMI (National Alliance on Mental Illness)</strong>: Provides education, support, and advocacy for
        individuals and families affected by mental illness. <a href="https://www.nami.org/">Website</a></li>
      <li><strong>Mental Health America</strong>: Offers resources, screening tools, and information on mental health
        conditions. <a href="https://www.mhanational.org/">Website</a></li>
      <li><strong>Headspace</strong>: Provides guided meditation and mindfulness exercises to help manage stress and
        anxiety. <a href="https://www.headspace.com/">Website</a></li>
      <li><strong>Kids Help Phone</strong>: Canada's 24/7 support service for youth, offering counseling, information,
        and referrals. <a href="https://kidshelpphone.ca/">Website</a></li>
      <li><strong>OK2Talk</strong>: Online community for teens and young adults struggling with mental health issues to
        share their stories and find support. <a href="https://www.ok2talk.org/">Website</a></li>
      <li><strong>Anxiety and Depression Association of America (ADAA)</strong>: Offers information and resources on
        anxiety, depression, and related disorders. <a href="https://adaa.org/">Website</a></li>
      <li><strong>Teen Mental Health</strong>: Provides resources, tools, and information specifically designed for
        teenagers. <a href="https://teenmentalhealth.org/">Website</a></li>
      <li><strong>Mind</strong>: UK-based mental health charity offering information, support, and advocacy. <a
          href="https://www.mind.org.uk/">Website</a></li>
      <li><strong>The Jed Foundation</strong>: Focuses on emotional health and preventing suicide among college and
        university students. <a href="#">Website</a></li>
    </ol>
